branchItem.description:
&lt;p&gt;
Low friction characteristics are improved with the use of the CQ2X low speed cylinder series. Minimum operating pressure is cut in half,  compared to previous series, while achieving stable thrust.  All microspeed cylinders have  the same dimensions as the standard cylinders.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
The CQSX series is a microspeed cylinder that  allows low speed transfer of work pieces that  cannot tolerate shock.  CQSX is capable of  smooth starts with minimal lurching even after long periods of no operation.  All models have the same dimensions as the standard cylinders.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
The CUX series low speed type free mount cylinder saves  space and allows direct and precise mounting.  It is  available in 10mm to 32mm bore sizes with stroke lengths  up to 50mm.  Specifications include, double acting single rod, non-lube type cylinder, double side rubber bumpers and basic type mounting.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
The CM2X series is a microspeed cylinder designed to minimize operating pressure while achieving  stable thrust.  The operating pressure is cut in  half compared to previous series.  All models have the same dimensions as the standard cylinders.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
The CJ2X microspeed cylinder series operates smoothly with minimal stick-slip.  This series achieves stable low speed operation even at 0.5 mm/s (1mm/s for &#xf8;16 or smaller).  The average  speed is obtained by dividing the stroke by the  piston rod movement time.  All models have the  same dimensions as the standard cylinders.
&lt;/p&gt;
